adaptive shift?
    the idea would be to allow the search window to shift +x/-x as some rows are thin
    width of any given row would be limited
    unsure how to avoid finding the same essential next row with different shift values
    could generate all possible next row windows (even shorter) and insist each result "fill" its window (refuse when row finishes if it didn't fill its window?)
    as a very cheap version of this we could have fixed shifts computed from center of last row's bounding box
        this way there's no forking in window so no overlap problem

checkpoint to disk?
    tree structure is generally resumable
    unclear how to manage lifecycle in CLI...
    maybe take directory to run in, dump results there, resume/checkpoint state there, etc.

optimize...
